at|mitche: Play:  I have a problem with the opening lead:
Don’t lead an unsupported Ace in a side suit against a suit contract, especially when the opps have bid to a voluntary game.
Look at it this way: 
E/W have 24 or 25 HCP, probably, maybe more. North has 10 HCP. 
That leaves at most 6 HCP for South here.
So it is much more likely that E/W have the @SK than not.|
pg| ***** 46 ***** |


nt||
at|mitche:  So leading the ace captures air.
Better to lead the @DK.
Set up a winner, and hope partner can contribute to the defense in some useful way.|
