West can see that South can't have a quick entry.
So by leading the @H10 (say it doesn’t get covered by south) and it loses to the @HJx in north.
A @D comes back, you win the Ace, and then lead another heart from dummy, playing the @hAK now.  
If hearts were 3-2, you are still OK.  
But if they're 4-1 you save a trick (unless you lose to a singleton Q or J).|
